4.20	History_of_Saturday_Night_Live_(1975-1980)	History of Saturday Night Live (1975â€“1980)	Perhaps due to his recurring news parody sketch "Weekend Update" (which survives to this day, albeit with new anchors), Chevy Chase was the first breakout star of SNL, garnering magazine covers, in-depth interviews, and even some speculation that he would succeed Johnny Carson if Carson ever left The Tonight Show (eventually, Chase did host his own talk show, but it failed miserably and was cancelled after five weeks).	
